## Fraud Detection

# About
I analyzed credit card transactions to detect fraudulent activity
using machine learning models.

#Dataset
Credit card transactions dataset with 10,000 records.
Only 1% transactions are fraudulent - class imbalance problem.

# Steps I followed
1. Loaded and explored the dataset
2. Checked class distribution
3. Split data into train and test
4. Trained 3 models and compared accuracy
5. Visualized results using confusion matrix

#Results
Logistic Regression | 99.89% |
<br>
Decision Tree | 99.93% |
<br>
Random Forest | 99.97% |

# What I learned
- Class imbalance makes accuracy misleading
- Random Forest works best for fraud data
- Confusion matrix is more useful than accuracy here

# Tools Used
Python, Pandas, Scikit-learn, Seaborn, Matplotlib
